WEBVTT

00:01.252 --> 00:03.731
- Hello, Ms. Goderitch.
- KRYSTAL: <i>What happened to your voice?</i>

00:03.755 --> 00:05.632
Nothing. This is my truth voice.

00:05.799 --> 00:07.384
FELIX: <i>She's more than suspicious.</i>

00:07.509 --> 00:10.149
<i>She's investigating this shit,
she's starting to piece it together.</i>

00:10.303 --> 00:12.013
SUSAN: Krystal is a naive subject.

00:12.138 --> 00:15.141
She has some delusions about her
circumstance, but she's harmless.

00:15.433 --> 00:16.559
Gotta keep her on the move.

00:16.643 --> 00:19.062
I thought my DNA
was supposed to make it better.

00:19.145 --> 00:20.814
It takes time to develop a therapy.

00:21.064 --> 00:23.650
You don't wanna go sticking your neck
out for the Hendrixes.

00:23.733 --> 00:24.733
And why's that?

00:24.776 --> 00:26.212
He says they're dealing pills
out of Bubbles.

00:26.236 --> 00:29.781
I created you as a beautiful baseline.

00:30.031 --> 00:31.550
- (GROANING)
<i>- You've seen the alternative.</i>

00:31.574 --> 00:33.284
<i>The carriers? The device</i>

00:33.618 --> 00:34.619
<i>in Sarah?</i>

00:34.869 --> 00:37.455
But share the original's genome,

00:38.957 --> 00:40.583
and together, we can make a cure.

00:40.792 --> 00:42.168
Beth, what the hell are you doing?

00:42.502 --> 00:45.342
Now, you're off the case. But you keep
digging, and digging and digging.

00:46.423 --> 00:47.424
You can do this.

01:08.737 --> 01:09.821
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:12.949 --> 01:14.784
SECURITY GUARD: Your ID, please.

01:14.868 --> 01:17.162
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- (PIANO MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY)

01:18.163 --> 01:19.497
Your ID, please.

01:29.174 --> 01:30.508
Ma'am, your ID.

01:31.509 --> 01:33.845
- (SCANNER BEEPS)
- Thank you.

01:54.115 --> 01:56.409
I'm glad the morale is good.

01:56.493 --> 02:00.413
Two dead test subjects
in as many weeks is not.

02:00.497 --> 02:01.998
We've got it under control.

02:02.081 --> 02:05.752
What good are your implants
if patients keep tearing them out?

02:10.882 --> 02:12.759
(INDISTINCT)

02:15.512 --> 02:17.138
- Thank you.
- (GLASS SHATTERING)

02:17.222 --> 02:18.223
SUSAN: Oh, dear!

02:20.725 --> 02:21.786
- Uh, never mind...
- Here, Susan.

02:21.810 --> 02:24.229
...I'll just go find
someplace to wash up.

02:34.447 --> 02:36.282
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

02:39.702 --> 02:40.912
Susan Duncan.

02:43.373 --> 02:44.582
I know you.

02:46.459 --> 02:47.460
I know everything.

02:51.130 --> 02:52.924
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:25.331 --> 03:27.417
IRA: Are you ready to meet our original?

03:27.500 --> 03:29.961
After all these years... (SIGHS DEEPLY)

03:30.044 --> 03:31.838
I feel electric.

03:31.921 --> 03:34.841
And when it's done? When I have my cure?

03:36.426 --> 03:40.680
Perhaps we could go back
to Tristan da Cunha.

03:40.763 --> 03:42.765
The summer you rescued me from Yale.

03:43.766 --> 03:44.851
I was researching

03:44.976 --> 03:49.105
the pathogenesis of rare disorders,

03:50.106 --> 03:51.190
you remember?

03:51.274 --> 03:52.525
I remember the villa.

03:53.902 --> 03:55.570
With the lovely topaz roof.

03:56.195 --> 03:58.114
- It was red.
- Of course.

03:59.574 --> 04:01.868
What was the name of the town nearby?

04:02.952 --> 04:04.120
You're testing me.

04:04.662 --> 04:07.624
- I'm not glitching.
- I'm sorry.

04:08.333 --> 04:11.127
It's been two months
since your last cognitive exam.

04:11.210 --> 04:12.962
Hook me up right now.

04:13.046 --> 04:15.298
Test me if you'd like.

04:16.298 --> 04:18.426
We will never have to test you again,

04:22.012 --> 04:24.432
so long as Sarah listens to reason.

04:29.062 --> 04:32.649
Cosima, are we seriously considering
handing over Kendall's genetic material?

04:34.150 --> 04:35.777
<i>Susan gets to restart human cloning</i>

04:35.860 --> 04:38.488
<i>with new lab rats to study the genome.</i>

04:38.571 --> 04:41.240
<i>And in return,
you get that bot out of your face,</i>

04:41.324 --> 04:43.326
<i>and we get to collaborate on a cure.</i>

04:43.409 --> 04:45.411
Aren't you and Scott
well on your way to that?

04:48.498 --> 04:49.540
(CLICKS TONGUE)

04:49.624 --> 04:52.293
The last viral vector didn't work.

04:52.377 --> 04:54.754
<i>And even if the next one does...</i>

04:56.130 --> 04:58.299
I may not have that much time, Sarah.

05:02.387 --> 05:03.429
Okay.

05:04.347 --> 05:05.658
<i>So what are you gonna tell Siobhan?</i>

05:05.682 --> 05:06.683
(SIGHS)

05:06.766 --> 05:09.936
She's just gonna say no,
so I think we set it up first.

05:10.895 --> 05:11.896
Are you sure?

05:11.980 --> 05:14.691
<i>Yeah. It's not her life, is it?</i>

05:14.774 --> 05:15.984
<i>It's our decision.</i>

05:16.067 --> 05:17.110
(INHALES)

05:17.193 --> 05:19.278
<i>But we can't help them cure CASTOR.</i>

05:19.362 --> 05:21.030
If we give the Neos Kendall's genome,

05:21.114 --> 05:23.199
they'll have the sterilizing
pathogen again.

05:23.282 --> 05:24.325
(SIGHS)

05:25.243 --> 05:27.370
I may have a workaround,
but you're not gonna like it.

05:30.331 --> 05:32.333
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:36.087 --> 05:39.048
KRYSTAL: And I'm trying to,
like, change my life right now.

05:39.132 --> 05:42.010
Like, I shouldn't have
to live my life that way.

05:42.093 --> 05:43.511
I need protective custody now.

05:43.594 --> 05:46.681
Because if Dyad doesn't get me,
then Brightborn definitely will.

05:46.764 --> 05:48.364
All right. Can I have your name, please?

05:48.391 --> 05:50.101
(SIGHS) Krystal Goderitch.

05:50.184 --> 05:52.603
With a "K," in Krystal, obviously.

05:52.687 --> 05:55.732
Yeah, of course I'm available,
but you can't call me here.

05:55.815 --> 05:57.442
What kind of attitude did you expect?

05:57.525 --> 05:58.568
Hey.

05:58.651 --> 05:59.753
(KRYSTAL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

05:59.777 --> 06:00.937
ART: Mother or mistress, huh?

06:00.987 --> 06:02.739
DUKO: What are you doing, Arthur?

06:03.865 --> 06:06.492
Nothing. I just wanted to, uh...
(EXHALES)

06:06.576 --> 06:09.370
I wanted to thank you,
for warning me about the Hendrixes.

06:10.288 --> 06:13.791
Yeah, you're welcome.
Just, uh, just stay out of it.

06:16.753 --> 06:17.754
I'll do that.

06:17.837 --> 06:19.231
Are you taking any medications, ma'am?

06:19.255 --> 06:22.258
No. God, everyone thinks I'm crazy,

06:22.341 --> 06:23.843
or they try to get my number.

06:23.926 --> 06:26.387
Oh, you know what, Constable,
why don't I handle that for you?

06:27.180 --> 06:29.057
Hi, Detective Bell, homicide.

06:29.140 --> 06:31.726
Krystal Goderich, manicurist.

06:32.810 --> 06:34.830
You know, why don't we take
this somewhere more private?

06:34.854 --> 06:36.272
You're the boss.

06:38.733 --> 06:40.544
KRYSTAL: So I was kept in this room
for like an hour,

06:40.568 --> 06:43.029
and then they just
gave me free samples.

06:43.112 --> 06:44.173
Like, can you believe that?

06:44.197 --> 06:46.592
Like, I'm a whistle-blower,
I'm not gonna just, like, be paid off

06:46.616 --> 06:47.617
with free samples.

06:47.700 --> 06:50.369
Okay, wait, wait, wait.
Let's just back up for one second, okay?

06:50.453 --> 06:51.496
Certainly.

06:51.579 --> 06:52.639
These people who are after you...

06:52.663 --> 06:54.540
They're targeting beauty professionals.

06:55.416 --> 06:56.417
(STUTTERS) Right.

06:56.501 --> 06:58.711
Yeah, and some of us know
what they're actually doing,

06:58.795 --> 07:00.715
which is hoarding patents
in stem cell cosmetics.

07:00.755 --> 07:02.548
And totally testing on human beings.

07:02.632 --> 07:04.675
- Like, I'm against animal testing.
- Okay.

07:04.759 --> 07:06.803
Like, humans is, like, too far.

07:06.886 --> 07:08.721
- Do you know what I mean?
- Right.

07:13.392 --> 07:15.311
Does "LEDA" mean anything to you?

07:17.230 --> 07:19.107
Yeah. I love their eyeliner.

07:23.611 --> 07:24.612
Okay.

07:25.321 --> 07:27.281
CLERK: Dark Confidant
and Time Walk are key.

07:27.365 --> 07:29.367
I never play without them anymore.

07:29.450 --> 07:32.662
Most people think rare cards
must be awesome. Not so.

07:32.745 --> 07:34.831
Tell your son to play the game,
not the market.

07:34.914 --> 07:36.457
Stop pestering my driver.

07:36.541 --> 07:38.126
- No smoking.
- DRIVER: Here you go.

07:41.337 --> 07:42.797
Okay.

07:45.424 --> 07:46.634
Siobhan.

07:47.885 --> 07:49.595
I'm glad you're here.

07:50.847 --> 07:52.056
You all right, Ma?

07:53.349 --> 07:55.226
Because you're being really nice.

07:55.309 --> 07:57.270
It's about my other daughters.

07:58.563 --> 08:00.481
I'll let Cosima explain.

08:03.442 --> 08:04.443
EVIE: <i>Sarah Manning.</i>

08:04.527 --> 08:05.987
Welcome to Brightborn.

08:06.070 --> 08:07.405
You're Evie Cho, right?

08:08.322 --> 08:11.242
I'm gonna pass on the tour,
Cosima doesn't recommend it.

08:11.325 --> 08:14.162
- Did you come alone?
- No, I've got an army outside.

08:15.163 --> 08:18.875
If I'm not out in 20 minutes,
your original takes an acid bath.

08:18.958 --> 08:20.376
You understand?

08:20.459 --> 08:23.129
Then we better hurry. Susan's waiting.

08:26.465 --> 08:27.967
SARAH: Susan Duncan.

08:31.387 --> 08:33.597
Yeah, that's the same look
Leekie gave me.

08:33.681 --> 08:38.102
I'm sorry. It's just strange
to see an unfamiliar face.

08:38.644 --> 08:39.645
Is that a joke?

08:39.729 --> 08:40.770
No.

08:41.772 --> 08:42.940
You're a mystery to me.

08:43.024 --> 08:44.275
I like that.

08:47.153 --> 08:48.738
Christ, a CASTOR?

08:48.821 --> 08:51.073
Actually, I'm, uh, a Libra.

08:51.157 --> 08:53.242
This is Ira, my assistant.

08:53.326 --> 08:54.702
A breed apart.

08:54.785 --> 08:56.204
From what, Dobermans?

08:56.287 --> 08:58.414
I'm nothing like my brothers,
Ms. Manning.

08:58.497 --> 09:01.375
You're safe here. Sarah, please sit.

09:06.672 --> 09:10.051
Before we discuss Kendall, I wanna
know what this thing's doing to me.

09:10.134 --> 09:13.804
The devices do different things
for different subjects.

09:13.888 --> 09:15.973
For instance,
you mentioned Aldous Leekie.

09:16.057 --> 09:20.478
He had one treating a genetic
predisposition for Alzheimer's.

09:21.187 --> 09:22.230
But what's mine doing?

09:23.231 --> 09:24.357
It's making you sick.

09:25.233 --> 09:27.068
SUSAN: You're immune to the disease.

09:27.652 --> 09:31.948
By activating specific genes,
we hoped to isolate the illness.

09:32.031 --> 09:34.742
Apparently it hasn't flicked off
the right switch yet.

09:34.825 --> 09:36.702
(SIGHS) Why, 'cause I'm healthy?

09:36.786 --> 09:38.162
Because you're alive.

09:38.246 --> 09:39.914
SUSAN: We can have it out.

09:39.997 --> 09:42.708
We can start work on a cure today,

09:42.792 --> 09:45.044
if you just share Kendall.

09:45.127 --> 09:48.923
Only her unique biology
makes human cloning possible.

09:49.006 --> 09:51.842
Those same cells
could give you the CASTOR pathogen.

09:53.636 --> 09:55.680
So Cosima's come up with a solution.

09:57.014 --> 09:58.641
What kind of solution?

10:00.643 --> 10:02.061
Kendall Malone has cancer.

10:03.938 --> 10:05.356
Leukemia.

10:07.191 --> 10:08.734
(CLICKS TONGUE) Ma.

10:08.818 --> 10:12.238
You should've... (SNIFFLING)
You should've told me.

10:14.031 --> 10:17.785
And seen that look
for the rest of my life?

10:18.411 --> 10:21.455
(STUTTERING) We can get a doctor.

10:22.206 --> 10:24.792
I mean, someone we can trust
obviously and...

10:24.875 --> 10:27.628
Chicken, it's too late.

10:29.046 --> 10:31.215
And it's not your choice.

10:33.217 --> 10:34.593
(SIGHS)

10:34.677 --> 10:37.513
- (SNIFFLING)
- Cosima? Tell her what you told me.

10:41.475 --> 10:42.893
COSIMA: (SIGHING) Uh...

10:42.977 --> 10:45.563
Kendall's cancer might actually save us.

10:46.480 --> 10:48.774
SCOTT: Kendall's a chimera, right?

10:48.858 --> 10:51.360
Half her cells are CASTOR,
the other half are LEDA.

10:51.944 --> 10:53.863
No way to tell which was which.

10:54.530 --> 10:55.823
Until now.

10:55.906 --> 11:00.411
So you have all these white blood cells
and one of them goes nuts

11:00.494 --> 11:03.706
and starts multiplying like crazy,
millions of cancer cells.

11:03.789 --> 11:08.794
All of those are clones
of that first white blood cell.

11:08.878 --> 11:10.921
And luckily for us, the first one is...

11:11.005 --> 11:13.382
It's just got the LEDA, right?

11:13.466 --> 11:14.925
The LEDA genome.

11:15.009 --> 11:16.177
COSIMA: Yeah, exactly.

11:16.260 --> 11:18.888
So, if we isolate those leukemia cells,

11:20.222 --> 11:22.808
we don't give them CASTOR,
we only give them LEDA.

11:23.476 --> 11:24.852
(INHALES SHARPLY)

11:24.935 --> 11:28.647
An ingenious solution.
She's good, your sister.

11:28.731 --> 11:29.982
Self-made.

11:30.066 --> 11:32.234
Well, I can see an obvious problem.

11:32.318 --> 11:34.153
You're a biological weapon, mate.

11:35.321 --> 11:36.989
We're not saving CASTOR.

11:37.698 --> 11:38.949
Susan...

11:42.536 --> 11:44.121
Fetch me a hard drive, please.

11:45.998 --> 11:47.375
Ira, please.

11:53.881 --> 11:55.466
I accept your terms.

11:55.549 --> 11:58.677
But I want to be there
when the samples are taken from Kendall.

11:58.761 --> 11:59.762
I thought you might.

11:59.845 --> 12:01.490
And I want Cosima's research
on the disease

12:01.514 --> 12:03.057
transferred to my hard drive.

12:03.140 --> 12:04.326
She's closer to it than anyone,

12:04.350 --> 12:07.269
I think that her insights
will be valuable.

12:10.398 --> 12:12.608
You're not the first LEDA
to make it this far, you know.

12:12.691 --> 12:14.652
- What are you talking about?
- Ira.

12:18.864 --> 12:19.865
Beth?

12:20.741 --> 12:22.618
Beth thought she found her enemy.

12:22.701 --> 12:24.203
She was wrong.

12:25.037 --> 12:26.877
I hope you don't make
the same mistake she did.

12:32.294 --> 12:33.879
Put your hands up.

12:35.131 --> 12:36.632
How did you find me?

12:36.715 --> 12:39.051
I'm a cop. I have resources.

12:39.135 --> 12:40.636
I figured it out.

12:40.719 --> 12:43.097
You're the head of the snake.
You're where this all ends.

12:43.180 --> 12:45.099
You're mistaken.

12:45.182 --> 12:46.225
I'm your creator.

12:46.308 --> 12:48.227
- I'm invested.
- Shut up!

12:49.311 --> 12:51.522
Your mother's name is Ruth, isn't it?

12:51.605 --> 12:53.357
(INHALES SHARPLY)

12:53.441 --> 12:55.192
- Yes.
- Kind woman.

12:55.276 --> 12:57.611
Wanted a daughter more than anything.

12:57.695 --> 12:59.613
I was happy to oblige.

13:02.199 --> 13:03.909
We had no idea about your father.

13:04.535 --> 13:07.997
We screen for tendencies like that,
somehow he got through.

13:08.080 --> 13:09.415
- I'm sorry.
- Stop it!

13:10.374 --> 13:12.835
- You manipulate us. Turn around!
- We guide you.

13:14.128 --> 13:16.755
I saw you graduate. You recall?

13:16.839 --> 13:17.840
Get on your knees.

13:17.923 --> 13:20.009
You polished that badge
to a mirror shine.

13:20.092 --> 13:21.760
I said get down.

13:22.344 --> 13:23.471
Why are you doing this?

13:24.889 --> 13:27.558
If I kill you, it's over.

13:27.641 --> 13:32.021
The monitors. The testing.
(SIGHING) The lies.

13:32.104 --> 13:33.689
You control Neolution.

13:33.772 --> 13:35.983
No one controls the idea.

13:36.066 --> 13:38.027
Kill me and someone will take my place.

13:38.110 --> 13:40.571
But they will not protect you as I have.

13:42.448 --> 13:43.782
Protect us from what?

13:45.743 --> 13:47.369
From my own mistakes.

13:51.248 --> 13:53.584
Beth, whatever you think

13:53.792 --> 13:56.921
you know, you must believe this.

13:58.672 --> 14:03.052
I have devoted my life
to sustaining yours.

14:03.135 --> 14:06.138
(VOICE BREAKING) Without me,
your sisters will wither on the vine...

14:06.222 --> 14:08.057
(VOICE BREAKING) and I cannot bear that.

14:10.518 --> 14:12.686
I love you all.

14:13.646 --> 14:14.647
I love you.

14:14.730 --> 14:15.856
Close your eyes.

14:23.239 --> 14:24.406
(SHUDDERING)

14:39.713 --> 14:41.674
(PANTING)

14:48.639 --> 14:51.517
We knew Beth was in deep,
but trying to kill Susan Duncan...

14:52.726 --> 14:54.186
So what stopped her?

14:55.896 --> 14:59.441
Look at her. Another one thought
she could do it all on her own.

15:01.068 --> 15:02.653
We had to make a deal, S.

15:02.736 --> 15:06.907
You bartered my mother behind my back.

15:07.866 --> 15:10.953
Cosima needs a cure,
I need this bot out of my face.

15:11.036 --> 15:12.222
It's trying to make me sick, S.

15:12.246 --> 15:14.707
Not just your neck's
on the line though, is it, Sarah?

15:14.790 --> 15:16.208
Kendall agreed to it.

15:16.292 --> 15:17.293
(SIGHS)

15:17.376 --> 15:19.295
I just got her back.

15:19.837 --> 15:20.921
Mum.

15:22.256 --> 15:23.882
I'm sorry.

15:23.966 --> 15:25.301
I will do my part.

15:25.384 --> 15:28.596
I will keep Susan honest,
and everyone safe.

15:29.138 --> 15:31.223
But this is the wrong play, Sarah.

15:31.307 --> 15:33.017
You're putting us all at risk.

15:33.100 --> 15:35.102
You'll meet Scott at Fee's in an hour.

15:36.395 --> 15:37.688
Bring Benjamin.

15:48.282 --> 15:50.868
Leekie's Alzheimer's bot's looking
a little peaked.

15:50.951 --> 15:53.179
Suppose we should feed it some
blood, like <i>Little Shop of Horrors?</i>

15:53.203 --> 15:55.080
Yeah 'cause that ended well.

15:56.040 --> 15:57.291
Okay, here it is.

15:57.374 --> 15:59.209
One terabyte of data.

15:59.293 --> 16:02.796
Three months of blood, sweat,
and fluid samples.

16:03.505 --> 16:05.007
Two relationships.

16:06.258 --> 16:07.843
One missing soulmate.

16:07.926 --> 16:11.221
Well, Shay was a rebound,
so one-and-a-half relationships.

16:12.389 --> 16:14.224
One-and-three-quarters tops.

16:14.308 --> 16:16.101
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

16:17.811 --> 16:20.064
COSIMA: I just don't know
if sharing this is a win, or...

16:20.898 --> 16:22.232
Surrender?

16:24.526 --> 16:27.488
We would have cracked it,
if we had the time.

16:28.614 --> 16:29.740
Yeah.

16:32.034 --> 16:33.535
- Yeah, let's do this.
- Yeah.

16:37.164 --> 16:40.542
LEDA is everything.
I wish you'd understand.

16:40.626 --> 16:42.086
I do understand.

16:43.337 --> 16:46.173
You need your girls
to build a better human.

16:46.256 --> 16:48.008
My life is expendable.

16:48.092 --> 16:51.637
Oh, please. Don't talk like that.

16:56.225 --> 16:58.060
I don't wanna die, Susan.

16:59.061 --> 17:00.688
I wanna be with you.

17:05.901 --> 17:07.736
(SUSAN SIGHS)

17:07.819 --> 17:11.531
I will find a way, for you as well.

17:12.156 --> 17:13.492
I promise.

17:15.828 --> 17:17.371
You believe me?

17:27.256 --> 17:28.757
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

17:30.676 --> 17:31.969
Sarah, I don't get it.

17:32.052 --> 17:36.223
I'm sorry, Art, I think when Beth
couldn't pull the trigger on Susan,

17:36.306 --> 17:37.725
she just couldn't live with it.

17:37.808 --> 17:39.643
<i>No, I watched that video hundred times.</i>

17:39.727 --> 17:41.937
The wig, the gun.

17:42.020 --> 17:43.081
And then she comes back again.

17:43.105 --> 17:44.708
I mean, if she didn't
shoot anybody then...

17:44.732 --> 17:47.025
- Why did she have blood on her hands?
<i>- Exactly.</i>

17:47.109 --> 17:48.444
(KNOCKING ON GLASS)

17:50.529 --> 17:51.822
What about this thing here?

17:52.740 --> 17:54.783
Krystal thinks
Vidal Sassoon's after her.

17:54.867 --> 17:56.160
Krystal, shit.

17:56.243 --> 17:58.746
Uh, I'll get Fee to call you, all right?

17:58.829 --> 18:01.206
- He's, uh, got a way with her.
<i>- Okay.</i>

18:01.290 --> 18:03.059
You sure you and Cosima
don't need backup at Brightborn?

18:03.083 --> 18:04.543
No, we've got it covered.

18:04.626 --> 18:06.336
I should be bot-less in an hour.

18:07.129 --> 18:08.547
Sarah, you watch your back.

18:09.465 --> 18:11.049
This is what killed Beth.

18:17.347 --> 18:20.392
Arthur, this is a hare-brained scheme,
who would buy it?

18:20.976 --> 18:23.979
Actually, Krystal.
Okay, yeah, fine, I'll be there soon.

18:26.398 --> 18:27.691
Susan's en route.

18:27.775 --> 18:29.902
You call me when you're done
with the hairdresser.

18:29.985 --> 18:31.195
She's an aesthetician.

18:31.278 --> 18:33.906
We need to keep this situation
under control, Fee.

18:33.989 --> 18:36.325
Just promise me that Adele
is not gonna walk in.

18:36.408 --> 18:38.744
It's a moot point, she went home.

18:38.827 --> 18:42.623
Felix, when this is all done,
bring her back.

18:42.706 --> 18:44.958
I want the whole family here for Ma.

18:45.042 --> 18:46.251
Everyone.

18:48.253 --> 18:49.880
Kendall's a tough old badger, Mum.

18:49.963 --> 18:51.131
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

18:51.215 --> 18:53.008
Okay? You've still got time.

18:54.051 --> 18:56.178
- BENJAMIN: They're coming up.
- Yeah.

18:59.389 --> 19:00.390
They're here.

19:01.642 --> 19:02.810
You all set?

19:02.893 --> 19:06.522
Ready to separate the original's cells.
Just need one original.

19:09.608 --> 19:10.609
(KNOCKING)

19:10.692 --> 19:12.778
- Ma?
- (TOILET FLUSHING)

19:12.861 --> 19:14.154
Showtime.

19:23.705 --> 19:25.207
SUSAN: Mrs. Malone.

19:25.290 --> 19:26.750
It's an honor.

19:30.170 --> 19:32.923
Maybe this isn't such
a good idea after all.

19:33.006 --> 19:35.467
Hey. We're gonna get
that thing out of your face.

19:35.551 --> 19:37.261
- Uh-huh.
- Okay?

19:37.344 --> 19:39.239
- Then we'll take you for ice cream...
- (SARAH SCOFFS)

19:39.263 --> 19:40.722
...if you're good.

19:40.806 --> 19:44.351
The extraction is safe, but delicate.

19:44.434 --> 19:46.770
We'll put you under.
You'll sleep right through it.

19:46.854 --> 19:49.314
- No. Not her.
- Why not?

19:49.398 --> 19:52.025
I can still taste
your partner's fingers in my mouth.

19:53.151 --> 19:54.820
COSIMA: Yeah, I'm assisting.

19:55.779 --> 19:57.072
I got your back.

20:01.076 --> 20:02.953
You can watch Scott work from there.

20:05.664 --> 20:06.874
Take a seat.

20:09.084 --> 20:10.085
Thank you.

20:10.168 --> 20:11.169
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

20:11.253 --> 20:13.547
MRS. S: Cosima says they've started.

20:14.464 --> 20:16.925
Last needle, I promise.

20:17.009 --> 20:18.051
(KENDALL GASPS)

20:19.219 --> 20:22.097
Do you know why your biology
is so unique, Mrs. Malone?

20:22.180 --> 20:24.016
Just my bloody luck.

20:24.683 --> 20:26.310
Yes, you're a true anomaly.

20:26.393 --> 20:29.479
The only clonable subject
my husband ever found.

20:29.563 --> 20:31.815
No wonder he hid your identity so well.

20:32.399 --> 20:34.026
Hid me from the likes of you.

20:35.027 --> 20:36.194
Ethan saw the best in people.

20:36.278 --> 20:37.738
I see the most.

20:37.821 --> 20:41.992
And right now, you are the
most valuable person in the world.

20:55.047 --> 20:57.591
COSIMA: What are those striations?
Nerves?

20:57.674 --> 21:01.011
Neuromorphic grid,
biofeedback, not hardcoding.

21:01.094 --> 21:02.471
More resilient that way.

21:02.554 --> 21:04.056
So it has instincts?

21:04.139 --> 21:05.182
(MUMBLES)

21:05.265 --> 21:07.476
- Sorry.
- Syringe?

21:07.559 --> 21:08.602
Yeah.

21:14.900 --> 21:15.901
(EVIE SIGHS)

21:15.984 --> 21:20.155
The implant reacts
to heat and pressure variance.

21:20.238 --> 21:22.950
This enzyme neutralizes those receptors.

21:23.033 --> 21:25.661
Puts it to sleep. No toxic failsafe.

21:26.203 --> 21:27.287
Forceps.

21:30.958 --> 21:32.501
COSIMA: There you go.

21:34.336 --> 21:36.046
You're doing really well, Sarah.

21:36.713 --> 21:38.006
Almost there.

21:41.009 --> 21:42.844
EVIE: Ugh. It's leaking toxin.

21:42.928 --> 21:45.128
- I can't extract without rupturing it.
- (SARAH GRUNTS)

21:45.639 --> 21:46.723
(SOFTLY) You're okay.

21:46.807 --> 21:48.934
- Okay, we plug the leak, right?
- EVIE: Yes.

21:49.017 --> 21:50.811
- Just breathe, Sarah.
- (GRUNTING)

21:50.894 --> 21:53.355
If that toxin hits
her blood stream, she's dead.

21:53.438 --> 21:55.148
Okay. Here we go. Don't move.

21:55.232 --> 21:56.918
- Don't move.
- EVIE: It's tearing. Now or never.

21:56.942 --> 21:59.111
COSIMA: Don't move.
EVIE: Careful.

21:59.778 --> 22:00.779
Okay...

22:02.572 --> 22:05.283
All right, now pull it out
very, very carefully.

22:07.619 --> 22:09.287
(SOFTLY) Slowly, slowly.

22:10.497 --> 22:12.708
Good. (INHALING DEEPLY)

22:16.503 --> 22:19.423
Good job. Great. (SOFTLY) Great.

22:19.506 --> 22:21.633
(GASPING)

22:25.303 --> 22:26.638
(SPITTING)

22:27.139 --> 22:28.765
(GASPING CONTINUES)

22:32.477 --> 22:33.645
You said it was safe.

22:33.770 --> 22:36.106
You must have damaged it
trying to remove it.

22:38.942 --> 22:40.861
Hey, you did it.

22:40.944 --> 22:42.279
(SARAH GROANS)

22:44.656 --> 22:46.324
I'm ready to aspirate the cancer cells.

22:50.871 --> 22:52.080
I'm so sorry.

22:52.164 --> 22:54.624
(SCOFFS) You're getting
what you want, aren't you?

22:55.459 --> 22:58.045
I'd spit, but she'd probably bottle it.

22:59.629 --> 23:01.173
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

23:01.798 --> 23:04.176
- MRS. S: <i>What's happening?</i>
- It's out. I'm coming.

23:04.301 --> 23:06.011
- Get Kendall on the move.
<i>- Okay.</i>

23:06.136 --> 23:07.471
Is Cosima still with Evie?

23:07.554 --> 23:10.724
She'll leave Brightborn
as soon as Susan has her samples.

23:10.807 --> 23:11.850
<i>Okay.</i>

23:12.517 --> 23:14.936
Finish up, Scott. You're done, Ma.

23:15.020 --> 23:16.480
Benjamin!

23:19.191 --> 23:21.985
Before you leave, Mrs. Malone,
I want to thank you.

23:22.069 --> 23:26.073
You won't live to see it, but you have
given us all a better future.

23:27.157 --> 23:28.325
Let's go.

23:29.576 --> 23:33.413
(STAMMERS) I'll see you later, Ma.
You... You did good.

23:34.414 --> 23:36.333
Watch her. It's not over.

23:52.682 --> 23:55.185
- You got that lighter?
- Yeah.

24:03.401 --> 24:06.780
Wham! I popped that husky
masseur right onto his behind.

24:06.863 --> 24:08.341
But he must have had
backup or something,

24:08.365 --> 24:09.675
and she must have had a green belt,

24:09.699 --> 24:12.220
'cause she, like, had me in an arm
lock before I could even block it.

24:12.244 --> 24:13.954
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

24:14.037 --> 24:15.080
(WHISPERS) Okay.

24:15.205 --> 24:17.749
- Is that your guy?
- Listen, just relax, okay?

24:18.250 --> 24:20.961
This guy knows more about this
than anybody alive.

24:22.254 --> 24:23.380
Hello!

24:24.381 --> 24:26.341
- What the hell are you wearing?
- FELIX: What?

24:26.424 --> 24:28.802
International intrigue lacks flair.

24:28.885 --> 24:31.471
Look, I just need to know
that you can do this, all right?

24:31.555 --> 24:33.098
I don't want her to rabbit on us.

24:33.223 --> 24:35.392
She's not gonna rabbit, okay?
It's gonna be fine.

24:36.601 --> 24:38.228
- Krystal...
- Oh, my God!

24:38.311 --> 24:39.705
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Oh, my God!

24:39.729 --> 24:42.941
You're that guy who stole my wallet
right before I was kidnapped.

24:43.733 --> 24:45.360
- Oh, yeah.
- Um, well, Krystal,

24:45.443 --> 24:48.738
- this is, um, Inspector Dawkins.
- (SNAPPING FINGERS)

24:48.822 --> 24:49.865
From the Yard.

24:49.948 --> 24:51.575
What yard?

24:52.117 --> 24:53.743
- Scotland Yard.
- FELIX: Yes.

24:54.411 --> 24:55.412
Oh.

24:55.495 --> 24:56.746
He's a cop.

24:57.664 --> 24:58.707
From London.

24:58.790 --> 24:59.916
You said Scotland.

25:00.000 --> 25:02.669
Okay, that's as far as that's gonna go.

25:02.752 --> 25:06.131
Krystal, truth voice, right?

25:07.257 --> 25:09.759
Do you remember what I said
to you the first time we met?

25:10.927 --> 25:13.346
- That I wasn't alone?
- FELIX: That's right, darling.

25:13.430 --> 25:15.432
And you're not alone in... Oh, my God!

25:15.515 --> 25:17.642
- Oh, Jesus!
- Oh, God, it burns!

25:17.767 --> 25:19.394
- Oh, shit.
- ART: Put the mace away!

25:19.477 --> 25:21.104
- I'm... I...
- Put it away!

25:21.188 --> 25:23.481
(FELIX GROANING) What is wrong with you?

25:23.607 --> 25:24.608
Ugh!

25:46.713 --> 25:48.465
- You all right, Sarah?
- Brilliant.

25:50.300 --> 25:51.968
- Susan.
- Hello, Sarah.

25:52.052 --> 25:54.304
- How are you, love?
- Been better.

25:54.387 --> 25:56.723
- These are done? The samples?
- Uh, 52 LEDA cells.

25:56.806 --> 25:58.391
Just enough for a sustainable line.

25:58.475 --> 26:01.394
Which I will hand over
once I get confirmation Cosima is free.

26:01.478 --> 26:03.230
She's remarkable, Cosima.

26:03.313 --> 26:05.565
I wish Rachel had
such an inquiring mind.

26:05.649 --> 26:07.234
They're all so different.

26:07.317 --> 26:10.111
- Yeah, you have no idea.
- SCOTT: Whoa! Whoa, is that bleach?

26:10.195 --> 26:12.155
- Are you out of your mind?
- Benjamin!

26:13.073 --> 26:14.532
BENJAMIN: Thought I smelled trouble.

26:14.658 --> 26:17.285
You've just destroyed yourself,
you stupid girl!

26:17.369 --> 26:19.537
Sarah, you wanna tell us
what you're doing?

26:19.663 --> 26:21.665
SUSAN: Kendall's driver's not answering.

26:22.374 --> 26:24.209
I found her cigarettes
in a pool of blood.

26:25.168 --> 26:26.211
Bathroom.

26:27.504 --> 26:29.798
- What have you done?
- I haven't done anything.

26:29.881 --> 26:31.925
Bollocks! Where's my mother?

26:32.008 --> 26:34.886
If anything's happened, it wasn't me.

26:35.011 --> 26:37.347
(SIGHS) We have to go, S.

26:38.348 --> 26:39.766
Yeah, you're coming with us.

26:40.433 --> 26:42.394
And your life depends
on what happens next.

26:42.519 --> 26:44.646
- Do you understand me?
- Not just mine.

26:44.729 --> 26:47.357
What about Cosima?
She's still at Brightborn.

26:47.857 --> 26:51.569
EVIE: The power source is metabolic,
from the host's own tissue.

26:52.404 --> 26:54.239
A synthetic ATP chain.

26:55.031 --> 26:57.575
Nature is just a set
of spare parts to you, isn't it?

26:57.701 --> 26:59.786
Well, I think of it more as a palette.

27:00.370 --> 27:01.705
Your research?

27:10.922 --> 27:13.091
Tell me what happened
to Delphine Cormier.

27:13.967 --> 27:15.051
Who?

27:16.303 --> 27:17.887
The former head of Dyad.

27:18.930 --> 27:22.726
Oh. Doctor Cormier. Of course.

27:22.809 --> 27:24.644
Dyad's not my purview.

27:24.728 --> 27:28.273
I'm sorry. But I knew of her
and her dedication to you.

27:28.398 --> 27:29.941
Yeah, that's what I'm afraid of.

27:30.567 --> 27:32.736
It's her research on there too,
isn't it?

27:33.653 --> 27:34.922
I couldn't have done it without her.

27:34.946 --> 27:37.073
And what you started together,

27:38.408 --> 27:40.327
we can all finish with Kendall's genome.

27:47.250 --> 27:48.418
Susan's gone dark.

27:49.127 --> 27:51.755
- What? What's going on?
- (CELL PHONE RINGING)

27:58.261 --> 28:00.263
- (FELIX GROANS)
- KRYSTAL: I'm so sorry.

28:00.347 --> 28:03.641
I'm taking self-defense classes,
so it was just, like, a reflex.

28:03.725 --> 28:05.018
Oh, is that what happened?

28:05.101 --> 28:08.104
- I have Visine in my bag if you want it.
- Nope, that's all right.

28:08.188 --> 28:10.148
Uh, nothing more from your purse.

28:10.231 --> 28:11.858
- (FELIX GROANS)
- (SOFTLY) Okay.

28:11.941 --> 28:14.527
Listen, just pull yourself
together, okay? She's scared.

28:15.445 --> 28:16.571
Buck up.

28:17.489 --> 28:18.490
(ART SIGHS)

28:19.532 --> 28:20.658
(FELIX SIGHING) Oh, God.

28:22.118 --> 28:24.204
Aw, your poor skin.

28:24.287 --> 28:27.290
- No, really, it's just a flesh wound.
- I'm so bad.

28:27.374 --> 28:28.750
Look, Krystal...

28:29.834 --> 28:31.395
You need to know
that you figured it out.

28:31.419 --> 28:33.755
It's all true. All of it.

28:33.838 --> 28:37.884
There is this dirty war
being waged on stem cell technology,

28:37.967 --> 28:39.094
trying to control it,

28:39.177 --> 28:40.417
and it's all being orchestrated

28:40.553 --> 28:42.597
by the cosmetic companies.

28:44.641 --> 28:45.850
I knew it.

28:46.643 --> 28:49.646
Yes, yeah. All the big players
are involved. Right, Art?

28:49.729 --> 28:53.024
- Uh, Brightborn, Neolution...
- What's Neolution?

28:53.108 --> 28:54.943
- (STAMMERING)
- They're Swedish.

28:55.026 --> 28:56.736
- Oh.
- Yes, quite European.

28:56.820 --> 28:59.406
- Oh, God.
- Look, Krystal, the point is,

28:59.489 --> 29:03.535
while the case is still open,
you need to just live your life

29:03.618 --> 29:05.537
as normally as possible. Go home.

29:05.620 --> 29:07.330
They can't know we're onto them.

29:08.081 --> 29:09.374
(GRUNTS)

29:09.457 --> 29:11.459
Our numbers are in here.

29:11.543 --> 29:13.378
For emergencies only, though.

29:15.296 --> 29:17.173
- Are you okay? I keep...
- (FELIX GROANS)

29:17.257 --> 29:20.760
Ever since I smacked
this French doctor at the Dyad,

29:20.844 --> 29:24.347
I just keep injuring people
everywhere I go. I'm so sorry.

29:24.431 --> 29:26.099
Do you mean Dr. Delphine Cormier?

29:27.267 --> 29:28.518
Why, do you know her?

29:28.601 --> 29:29.936
Is she involved in this?

29:30.895 --> 29:32.188
Well, she's a friend of ours.

29:33.022 --> 29:34.607
What can you tell us about her?

29:35.525 --> 29:37.402
I'm so sorry, um...

29:39.946 --> 29:41.156
I saw her get shot.

29:44.075 --> 29:45.493
I saw everything.

29:58.715 --> 30:00.467
MRS. S: No one will find you here.

30:02.260 --> 30:04.179
Where is she? Where's Kendall?

30:04.262 --> 30:07.974
You think I'd kidnap Kendall and then
allow myself to be taken hostage?

30:08.057 --> 30:09.851
You'll do anything.

30:09.934 --> 30:12.020
You hunted her down for 20 years.

30:12.103 --> 30:13.730
- It wasn't me!
- (SCOFFS)

30:13.813 --> 30:15.040
It doesn't make sense, does it?

30:15.064 --> 30:16.167
You don't actually believe her?

30:16.191 --> 30:19.027
She's got the genome,
she doesn't need to do this.

30:21.321 --> 30:22.572
But Ira does.

30:23.698 --> 30:24.741
No.

30:25.283 --> 30:26.826
He was there when we made the deal.

30:26.910 --> 30:28.745
MRS. S: A deal that denied him a cure.

30:28.828 --> 30:30.705
He wouldn't betray me.

30:30.788 --> 30:32.832
Not even to save his own life?

30:34.250 --> 30:35.919
Where would we find him?

30:42.383 --> 30:44.802
There's a key card in my pocket.

30:46.054 --> 30:48.056
We keep rooms at the Palmina, 708.

30:51.184 --> 30:53.686
You got my ma into this.
You better get her out.

30:54.938 --> 30:56.064
I'll go with her.

30:57.690 --> 30:58.816
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

31:13.831 --> 31:14.958
(GUN CLICKS)

31:16.501 --> 31:17.502
(DOOR BEEPS)

31:19.337 --> 31:21.339
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

31:27.971 --> 31:29.806
Shit. He's glitching!

31:30.932 --> 31:33.309
Hey, hey. Wake up! Where's Kendall?

31:34.561 --> 31:36.604
Hello, where's Kendall? Hey!

31:39.107 --> 31:40.275
Shit.

31:42.193 --> 31:44.445
Stupid bugger. He's OD'ing.

31:44.529 --> 31:46.990
- Call 9-1-1.
- (RETCHING)

31:47.073 --> 31:48.616
(SARAH GROANS)

31:49.534 --> 31:51.244
- (GAGGING)
- He's a dead end, Benjamin.

31:52.370 --> 31:53.705
Where's Kendall?

32:24.068 --> 32:25.612
So how're we doing back here?

32:37.582 --> 32:38.625
There you go.

32:39.834 --> 32:40.877
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

32:45.256 --> 32:46.424
Why am I out here?

32:47.175 --> 32:49.010
DUKO: It won't be long.

32:49.093 --> 32:50.970
If you're too cold,
I have a spare blanket.

32:51.929 --> 32:54.182
Nasty business
that we're wrapped up in, isn't it?

32:55.183 --> 32:56.768
Someone's got their hooks in ya.

32:57.393 --> 32:59.771
I've been hunted around the world.

32:59.854 --> 33:01.064
What's your story?

33:02.649 --> 33:04.150
I'm just in over my head, lady.

33:04.233 --> 33:05.711
(CHUCKLING) Just like everybody else.

33:05.735 --> 33:07.195
We can help you.

33:07.278 --> 33:09.405
My daughter, she hides people.

33:09.489 --> 33:10.865
How's that working out for you?

33:12.492 --> 33:14.702
Least I can look her in the eye.

33:16.287 --> 33:17.664
You're shivering.

33:18.373 --> 33:20.208
I'll get you that blanket.

33:24.504 --> 33:26.464
SARAH: Ira tried to kill himself.

33:26.547 --> 33:28.147
Benjamin's watching him at the hospital.

33:28.216 --> 33:29.526
He's had his stomach pumped, he's fine.

33:29.550 --> 33:32.762
Forget about Ira. What have
your vipers done with my mother?

33:32.845 --> 33:35.431
- S! S! S! That's enough.
- (SUSAN CHOKING)

33:36.057 --> 33:37.392
(COUGHING)

33:38.267 --> 33:39.394
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

33:41.437 --> 33:42.480
Scott?

33:43.064 --> 33:45.149
There's some kind of Trojan
wiping our research.

33:45.983 --> 33:48.486
Wha... How's that possible?
Your system's offline.

33:48.569 --> 33:51.155
It had to be introduced
on the hard drive from Brightborn.

33:55.076 --> 33:58.371
(BREATHING HEAVILY) Sarah, we're done.

33:59.997 --> 34:01.457
Everything's gone.

34:07.964 --> 34:09.924
Cosima's data's been wiped.

34:11.050 --> 34:12.385
It's a coup.

34:15.179 --> 34:18.558
- Competing technologies.
- I'm sorry, what's happening?

34:18.641 --> 34:21.351
Whoever did this doesn't care
about Kendall's genome.

34:21.436 --> 34:22.895
They just want LEDA destroyed.

34:23.438 --> 34:24.563
Who?

34:25.815 --> 34:27.400
The engineer.

34:30.277 --> 34:31.279
(SIGHS)

34:33.906 --> 34:35.324
EVIE: Mrs. Malone,

34:35.408 --> 34:37.159
you should've stayed hidden.

34:38.161 --> 34:42.123
I take it this is the one
who has you all twisted up.

34:42.206 --> 34:45.168
I'm sorry, it has to play out like this.

34:50.047 --> 34:53.259
(GASPS) You have your precious original.
Let her go.

34:55.678 --> 34:56.721
Stay there.

35:01.559 --> 35:05.521
This is compressed triethylaluminium.
Burns at 1,200 degrees.

35:06.814 --> 35:09.233
EVIE: And we've confirmed
all her samples are destroyed.

35:10.651 --> 35:12.278
There will be nothing left.

35:13.029 --> 35:14.113
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:14.197 --> 35:15.466
Susan, please, you have to tell us,

35:15.490 --> 35:17.241
where would Evie take Kendall?

35:18.451 --> 35:19.494
Beth.

35:19.577 --> 35:21.078
What are you talking about now?

35:21.162 --> 35:23.456
That's why she wanted to kill me.

35:23.748 --> 35:25.958
Beth held a gun to my head.

35:28.169 --> 35:29.962
And Evie put it in her hand.

35:37.970 --> 35:39.263
(PANTING)

35:39.972 --> 35:43.392
She didn't do it, Detective Duko.
She left Susan on her knees.

35:46.312 --> 35:48.856
- I'm in the car. Get down here.
- (CAR DOOR OPENS)

35:50.358 --> 35:52.235
- Beth...
- You set me up.

35:52.318 --> 35:53.861
(GASPING) No, I didn't.

35:53.945 --> 35:55.464
You... You said you wanted
to put an end to this,

35:55.488 --> 35:56.864
to free your sisters.

35:56.948 --> 35:59.116
By killing the head of Neolution.

35:59.200 --> 36:02.161
She made us. She needs us.

36:02.245 --> 36:05.289
Not you.
You just want to take her place.

36:05.373 --> 36:06.624
It's not happening!

36:06.707 --> 36:08.876
Oh, it is. I'll find another way.

36:08.960 --> 36:11.420
Susan's done, just like your sisters.

36:11.504 --> 36:14.841
- Don't talk about my sisters.
- Beth, you know too much now.

36:16.050 --> 36:19.262
If you run,
Neolution will cauterize your life.

36:19.345 --> 36:22.431
Alison, Cosima, your parents, Paul.

36:22.515 --> 36:25.059
- Then I'll pull the trigger right now.
- You won't end it.

36:25.142 --> 36:27.979
You wanna save the people that you love?

36:28.062 --> 36:29.814
Use that gun on yourself.

36:31.190 --> 36:32.775
Do you think I'm afraid to die?

36:35.444 --> 36:37.446
Do you think
I'm scared of anything right now?

36:44.871 --> 36:46.247
Why are you doing this?

36:48.583 --> 36:52.753
I never understood
what Susan saw in that face.

36:53.504 --> 36:56.132
In the decades of watching
your tedious lives,

36:56.215 --> 36:59.468
while technology just passed her by.

37:00.553 --> 37:03.014
Clones are obsolete.

37:04.473 --> 37:05.516
You're Betamax.

37:06.225 --> 37:07.643
Because of the bots?

37:07.727 --> 37:12.565
We don't need your baseline, we...
We can fix people now.

37:12.648 --> 37:14.483
You can't perfect the human genome.

37:14.567 --> 37:15.985
You can't know what perfect is!

37:16.068 --> 37:18.946
I know. I was born sick.

37:19.030 --> 37:22.158
I'm sick, too.
That doesn't justify this.

37:22.241 --> 37:25.953
Da Vinci robbed graves to study anatomy.

37:26.037 --> 37:29.916
In hundred years,
they'll call me a pioneer.

37:36.130 --> 37:37.840
Please don't do this.

37:38.716 --> 37:39.717
(SIGHING)

37:43.429 --> 37:44.639
Say goodbye.

37:46.432 --> 37:47.558
Quickly.

37:58.819 --> 38:00.613
- (SOFTLY) Please, please.
- Stop there.

38:05.326 --> 38:07.286
Kendall, what'll we do?

38:08.621 --> 38:10.164
No tears, Cosima.

38:11.999 --> 38:13.960
These shites aren't worth the salt.

38:16.671 --> 38:18.214
Tell Siobhan

38:19.590 --> 38:22.259
she's done right. Always.

38:23.970 --> 38:25.972
And tell your sisters

38:27.098 --> 38:29.392
I'm proud to have been part of them all.

38:31.268 --> 38:32.478
DUKO: Step back.

38:35.773 --> 38:37.024
(COSIMA SNIFFLES)

38:39.318 --> 38:40.903
KENDALL: Turn around, love.

38:41.862 --> 38:43.072
Turn around.

38:44.240 --> 38:45.449
Good girl!

38:47.535 --> 38:48.744
(GUNSHOT)

38:48.828 --> 38:50.246
(GASPING)

39:32.079 --> 39:35.124
Delphine Cormier was shot dead
at the Dyad parkade.

39:35.207 --> 39:37.001
(SOBBING) Oh, my God!

39:41.130 --> 39:44.341
Tell Susan the original's dead.

39:44.425 --> 39:46.385
Tell Sarah it's over,

39:47.845 --> 39:49.597
or Beth died for nothing.

40:02.735 --> 40:03.778
(SOBBING)

40:05.696 --> 40:07.823
(GRUNTING)

40:16.165 --> 40:17.708
DUKO: Beth!

40:17.792 --> 40:18.793
(PANTING)

40:20.377 --> 40:22.463
- Don't make me kill a cop.
- Don't make me.

40:23.881 --> 40:25.257
Is it true?

40:26.759 --> 40:28.677
Will my sisters die for what I know?

40:29.095 --> 40:30.471
DUKO: They've done it before.

40:32.014 --> 40:33.808
What's your play, Beth?

41:18.811 --> 41:21.897
It's over! We're done.
I'm done! I screwed it up.

41:22.898 --> 41:24.275
<i>We can't fight this anymore, Mika.</i>

41:27.611 --> 41:29.655
EVIE:
<i>Neolution will cauterize your life.</i>

41:29.738 --> 41:32.950
<i>Alison, Cosima, your parents, Paul.</i>

41:33.033 --> 41:35.369
<i>You wanna save the people that you love?</i>

41:35.870 --> 41:37.955
Use that gun on yourself.

41:38.998 --> 41:40.332
BETH: You need to drop all this.

41:41.375 --> 41:42.501
Go back into hiding.

41:43.294 --> 41:45.838
(SIGHING) <i>Drink iced tea,
play video games, whatever.</i>

41:45.921 --> 41:48.340
<i>Just stay hidden.</i>

41:48.424 --> 41:51.927
I have to keep everyone
that I care about safe.

41:52.011 --> 41:53.220
Please don't leave me.

41:54.054 --> 41:56.974
And you want that, too. Don't you, Beth?

41:58.184 --> 41:59.727
(SOFTLY) Watch the others for me.

42:18.829 --> 42:19.955
(SOBBING)

42:28.672 --> 42:31.342
(TRAIN APPROACHING)

42:36.931 --> 42:39.850
<i>♪ I will always follow
What is moving through my bodyline</i>

42:39.975 --> 42:42.412
<i>♪ I could never hold onto
something That doesn't stick inside ♪</i>

42:42.436 --> 42:43.437
(INHALING)

42:43.646 --> 42:45.731
You came to me an orphan.
That's all you'll ever be.

42:45.814 --> 42:46.815
(SOBBING)

42:50.444 --> 42:52.488
Welcome to <i>The Island of Doctor Moreau.</i>

42:52.696 --> 42:54.531
Listen to me,
because this is about Delphine.

42:56.325 --> 42:58.327
I wanted a bit of fun.
You can't even get it up.

42:58.577 --> 43:00.287
- She has a daughter?
- Sometimes.

43:03.207 --> 43:05.251
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
